# Shadcn/UI & Tailwind CSS Refactoring Plan

This document details the architectural path to rip out the initial vanilla CSS implementation and upgrade the entire frontend layer to **Tailwind CSS v3** coupled with **shadcn/ui**. This maximizes developer velocity, standardizes the design tokens, and sets the foundation for an easily scalable component library.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> Please review the sequence of the refactoring below. Ripping out Vanilla CSS requires touching almost every `.tsx` file we've written. The resulting aesthetic will be cleaner and heavily reliant on standard Shadcn patterns (Slate/Zinc dark mode, crisp borders). Let me know if you approve this architectural pivot!

## Proposed Changes

---

### Phase 1: Dependency Integration & Tooling
We will inject Tailwind and Shadcn tooling into the Next.js ecosystem.

#### [NEW] `tailwind.config.ts` & `postcss.config.mjs`
- Standard Tailwind v3 initialization. 
- Extension of the Tailwind theme to retain our "Synthetica" specific accent colors (Cyan/Neuro-glows) while leaning heavily on Shadcn themes.

#### [NEW] `components.json`
- Initialization of Shadcn mapping to `src/components/ui/` and `src/lib/utils.ts`.

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/globals.css`
- Delete all bespoke `.glass` and vanilla CSS resets.
- Replace entirely with Tailwind `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities;` and the Shadcn CSS-variable root map.

---

### Phase 2: Component Library Extraction (shadcn/ui)
Execution of the Shadcn CLI to pull in high-quality primitives to replace our `<button>` and basic divs.

- **[NEW]** `src/components/ui/button.tsx`
- **[NEW]** `src/components/ui/card.tsx`
- **[NEW]** `src/components/ui/table.tsx`
- **[NEW]** `src/components/ui/scroll-area.tsx`

---

### Phase 3: Dashboard & Layout Overhaul
Translating the custom JS inline-styles into optimized Tailwind Utility classes.

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/layout.tsx`
- Remove inline `style={{...}}`. Apply standard layout shells using flex utilities (`flex, h-screen, bg-background`).

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/page.tsx` (Dashboard)
- Refactor the sidebar "Raw Feed Inbox" into a Shadcn `ScrollArea`. 
- Upgrade the action buttons (`Trigger Live Scrape`, View Toggles) to utilize the Shadcn `<Button>` primitive with proper variants (e.g., `variant="outline"`, `variant="default"`).

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/settings/page.tsx`
- Convert the raw HTML tables into beautiful Shadcn `<Table>` components for managing the Configuration target lists.

---

### Phase 4: Polymorphic View Refactoring
Updating the specific content renders to match the standard.

#### [MODIFY] `NYTView.tsx`, `InstaScrollView.tsx`, `TikTokView.tsx`
- Remove all raw CSS objects.
- Use Tailwind utility classes for the dense typography spacing (e.g., `text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight`, `leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground`).
- Retain the distinct flavor of logic in each view (Carousel cards, vertical snap, editorial).

